Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for violation of the term and order of payment of goods (works, services) in the implementation of procurement for state and municipal needs.
This law is designed to solve a very acute problem of non-fulfillment of their obligations by customers in the implementation of state and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation when entrepreneurs could not receive payment for already executed state and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia instructed the Prosecutor General's Office of the Russian Federation to take the problem to special control.
Because businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers who concluded contracts that were not backed by financing, tried to evade the borrowed obligations of payment and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the whole country.
Since 2015, 9.7 thousand have been introduced in the interests of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders by the Prosecutor's Office. submissions, according to the results of their consideration, 4.5 thousand were brought to disciplinary responsibility. Officials, administrative - 533, to investigative bodies for the organization of procedural inspections presented 75 materials, 46 of them were opened criminal cases.
As a result, the debt to entrepreneurs in the amount of more than 66 billion rubles was repaid.
And these huge sums were not accumulated as a result of non-payment of multi-billion contracts.
Fable debts were led by numerous, systematic delays in paying for services to entrepreneurs for much more modest amounts.
Here is a characteristic case.
The head of a small company won a tender for the provision of services on social transportation for several million rubles.
The person has invested all his working capital, fully fulfilled the obligations, but the money put in time has not received.
The result is an increasing financial person from wage debts, taxes, loans that would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not apply for help to the prosecutor's office.
Now in some regions the problem was maximally leveled.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt under state and municipal contracts, revealed by prosecutors of subjects of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor's office operates in the mode of manual anti-crisis management.
The Prosecutor General personally conducts visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, on which all the violations and measures for their immediate elimination by prosecutors are thoroughly dealt with.
Such operational meetings were held this year in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg.
The implementation of the Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of Administrative Offenses of the Russian Federation regarding the establishment of administrative responsibility of the customer's officials for violation of the term and procedure for payment of goods (works, services) in the procurement for the provision of state and municipal needs, which was signed by the President of Russia last week.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia at the initiative of the Prosecutor General's Office.
The new law will complement the Code of Administrative Offenses of the Russian Federation with an article, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand. up to 50 thousand rubles for violation of the term and order of payment of goods, works and services at state and municipal procurement by the customer.
And if an official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offense, he will be disqualified for a period of one year to two years.
All prosecutors of subjects of the Russian Federation have already received instructions to ensure the application of these legislative novels in practice.
