The National Health Service of England has announced that the pre-exposition HIV prevention (PrEP), a tablet taken before sex, which, as proven, reduces the risk of infection in people at risk, an average of 86 percent, will now be provided by the health service during the initial three-year probation period of approximately 10,000 people.
She agreed to finance the test after the Court of Appeals supported last year the decision of the High Court, which stated that the National Health Service had the opportunity to pay PREP despite its statements that it should be financed by local authorities.
