On behalf of Vladimir Putin, the Presidential Human Rights Council has developed proposals to strengthen the independence of the judicial branch of power.
The LCC proposes to limit the powers of the chairmen of courts and to introduce their election.
For the courts of appeal and cassation instances of the SPH wants to introduce special districts that will not be tied to the administrative-territorial division in the Russian Federation.
The Supreme Court should also submit its proposals within the presidential order.
The SPH has completed the development of proposals that will strengthen the independence of the Russian justice.
