One of the ideas of the Kremlin human rights defenders is to limit the powers of the chairmen of courts to increase the independence of other judges.
If the candidate for the position of a judge has successfully passed the competition and received the support of the judiciary, the chairman of the court, in the opinion of the CCS, must submit him to his appointment, without the right to refuse, as the law allows now.
It is also proposed to deprive the chairman of the right to distribute cases for consideration between judges.
To do this, experts admit, can a specially written computer program.
