In order to protect judges from the pressure of regional administrations, the LCC proposes to re-organize appeals and cassation in courts of general jurisdiction.
Now their structure is tied to the administrative-territorial division in the Russian Federation.
The SPH says that "it is necessary to ensure the organization of individual courts of appeal and cassation instances not at the level of regional judicial bodies in subjects of the Russian Federation, but in judicial districts."
Experts take the practice of arbitration courts as the basis.
