"In Libya, we do not want to associate with any of the parties to the conflict"
The Russian authorities have recently intensified their policy in the Libyan direction, and with visits to Moscow, the delegations of the opposing Libyan parties have become part of the delegations.
The head of the Russian contact group for the intra-Lithuanian settlement under the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation and the State Duma, assistant to the head of the Chechen Republic Lev Dengov told Kommersant what goals Moscow pursues in this region and on whom he bets.
Almost nothing is known about the contact group in Libya that you are heading.
Here, say, the contact group on Ukraine - everyone knows about it.
And here - the veil of mystery.
What exactly do you do, what goals are you pursuing?
The contact group was established on the initiative of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation and the State Duma.
Its activities are supervised by Deputy Foreign Minister Mikhail Bogdanov and Adam Delimkhanov (deputy of the Duma from Chechnya. - "Sh").
The latter is authorized to work in the Libyan direction by the speaker of the State Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
The detainment of the Russian tanker Mechanic Cebotarev in Libya (in September 2015, there were 11 people on board. - "Sh").
We were thinking about how to help the crew.
Then a contact group of military specialists, representatives of the Duma was created, and head of Chechnya Ramzan Kadyrov supported our work.
And how did it happen that you headed it?
Since I have been working in Libya since 2008, I have been asked to lead the work of the group.
Our activities were not limited to the release of sailors with the Mechanic Chebotarev.
We managed to establish contacts with representatives of all major groups opposing each other in the Libyan conflict - and from Tripoli (where the recognized UN government headed by Faiz Saradzh is based. - "Sh"), and with Tobruck (the residence of the parliament, which opposes the government and supports Marshal Khaftar, who controls the eastern regions of Libya. - "Sh").
Thanks to the active participation of Ahmed Methig (Livia's Vice Prime Minister - Kommersant), we managed to quickly agree on the release of Russian sailors.
Then it was decided to use these contacts more effectively, to create a contact group.
Its task is to analyze the situation, identify key factors and players, dialogue with all parties to the conflict.
I would like to emphasize that in Libya we do not want to associate with any of the sides of the conflict, we are conducting a dialogue with everyone.
How many people are in the contact group and how many of them are constantly in Libya?
Now the contact group includes five people.
Among them there are people who have experience in security agencies, including the Defense Ministry.
We also want to introduce specialists in the region, representatives of the Institute of the Middle East of the Russian Academy of Sciences.
No one is constantly in Libya from our employees, so far there is no need.
Is there Russian military advisors and instructors in Libya now.
And if so, on whose side?
There are no Russian military specialists in Libya.
All conversations and publications about this are untrue.
But former military are included in your contact group...
Yes, and their presence is necessary.
For example, when we visit hot spots.
Or such closed to a certain point for us cities as Misrata (where the militia groups are based, played a role in overthrowing the Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011 and significantly intensified in the following years. - "Sh").
We arrived in Misurata in January this year.
We were frightened, they said that there are all Islamists, terrorists.
But it was important for us to evaluate the situation there, to analyze the real military potential, who is responsible for what, why there are rumors like the role of Islamists.
In Misurata we met with all the representatives of the detachments who were engaged in the destruction of ISIS in Sirta (in December 2016, this city on the Mediterranean coast was defeated by militants of the banned "Islamic state" in Russia - "Sh").
