And to what conclusion have you come to?
The "Islamic State" in Libya has not won Haftar?
This was not what he was doing.
Haftar conducted operations on another front, in Benghazi.
And ISIS in Sirta fought structures that obeyed the government in Tripoli.
And, by the way, we invited people who conducted this anti-terrorist operation to Russia.
And they arrived - the visit lasted from 19 to 23 April this year, the Libyan delegation was received by the Federation Council, the Duma, the Foreign Ministry and the Russian Guard.
As we have understood, you are in all Libyan regions and probably imagine the mood of local elites and field commanders.
Do you think that it will be possible to implement ceasefire agreements on holding elections that were reached in late July in Paris by Khalifa Haftar and Faiz Saraj?
Or again, as it has happened many times in the past, the agreements will be disrupted, the hostilities will resume, the parties will try to seize power alone?
For us, a good signal was the fact that Saraj and Haftar agreed to the next meeting, not so long ago it was impossible.
In the recent past, both leaders spoke very negatively about each other.
As for Russia's position...
