The successor of Mr. Okhlopkov will not be: the post of technical director is likely to be abolished, and the functionality is dispersed by the units of the CENCI.
The technical director of the Eastern and Deputy Director General of the Central Communications Service for Technological Development Andrei Okhlopkov told the top managers of several enterprises of the space industry, as well as an employee of the government apparatus.
"He has been working in the new post for several weeks," the interlocutors of "I" in the industry said.
It was not possible to get an operational comment on CENCI on Thursday, and Mr. Okhlopkov himself for comments was not available.
However, the information "K" was officially confirmed in the GKSPC.
He decided to move to the position of Director for Production Coordination, - said the company. - Andrey Okhlopkov set for him the task to ensure the launch minimum for the first launch at the Vostochny Cosmodrome has fully fulfilled.
Mr. Okhlopkov moved to work in the CENCI in 2013, having served in the space forces, in particular at Baikonur, and in Plesetsk - on the "northern" cosmodrome served as the first deputy commander in the rank of colonel.
In 2009, Andrei Okhlopkov became a defendant in a criminal case.
The investigation accused him of bribery: allegedly from his submission regional businessmen received state orders for resignation, but did not fulfill the obligations to clean the separated parts of launch vehicles in the Arkhangelsk region and the Republic of Komi.
In 2012, the jury found him innocent.
The responsibilities for technological development related to it in the CENCA were extended to various projects, but the main of them was the construction of the cosmodrome in the Far East.
Oleg Ostapenko, who then headed the Federal Space Agency, said in an interview with Kommersant that the situation in the East "was critical in October 2013."
The fact is that the planning made a strategic mistake: the completion of the construction and the first launch of the Soyuz-2.1 launch vehicle were planned at the same time - the end of 2015.
To launch before the end of the year, the construction was decided to be completed six months earlier and the terms were moved from December to July 2015.
To speed up the process had to go into cunning: the specialists of the CENCI began to conduct parallel installation of technological equipment at unfinished facilities.
The main supporter of this idea was Andrei Okhlopkov.
Despite the existing risks and still the transfer (instead of December 2015, the Soyuz flew only on April 28, 2016), this idea justified itself, says the source "K" at the cosmodrome: "Moreover, we would not have carried out a single launch from the East, but would be engaged in construction."
Deputy Prime Minister Dmitry Rogozin, who supervises the creation of the cosmodrome, jokingly called Andrei Okhlopkov his "cosmic Susanin," but it was he who almost always asked for information about the progress of the construction site.
Mr. Okhlopkov also remembered the directness: for example, in an interview with "K" he proposed to deprive the Federal Agency for Special Construction (Spetsstroy) of the status of the only performer in the Eastern and directly work with subcontractors: "Why should we put all the eggs in one basket of Special Construction?"
This idea has found support in the government.
Since 2017, CENKI has assumed the duties of the general contractor to complete the construction and installation works at the start and technical complex planned in the fourth quarter.
According to Kommersant, the reason for the transition of Mr. Okhlopkov to a new place of work was disagreements with the management of the Central Communications Service regarding the ways of completion of construction structures and cosmodrome complexes, as well as methods of work with subcontractors.
"It has been decided that this will be the best for everyone," says one of the top managers involved in the construction of the East.
The employee of the government apparatus, in turn, calls the decision strange: "He was one of the best specialists, it will be difficult to find an equivalent replacement for him."
According to Kommersant, this will not be necessary: the position of the technical director of the cosmodrome will be abolished, and its functions will be disposed of by the CENKI units.
