For walks around the city in a swimsuit or with a nude torso will now be fined 200 euros.
For 100 euros will be required from those who arrange a picnic in a public place or ride a bike in pedestrian areas, reports TASS with reference to the Association of Tour Operators of Russia.
In addition, it is mentioned that the authorities provide for a fine for inscriptions on monuments of 400 euros and for garbage 25 euros.
Inform tourists about the need to comply with the rules of conduct in Venice will be with the help of a special company "Address, respect Venice" (#EnjoyRespectVenezia) in social networks, as well as through ads and posters on the website of the city council, on billboards and in places of the largest crowd of tourists.
The campaign will be held in 10 languages.
According to the tourism advisor of Venice Paola Mar, the information about the fines will be transmitted to the embassies of native countries of violators, so as to warn their compatriots from such mistakes.
"The problem is that Venice is perceived as a beach," she said.
In April, the administration of the Italian city announced plans to limit the flow of tourists.
In Venice, there is already a successful restriction on the number of tourists visiting the city center.
Instead of 100,000 people who want to watch the Festa del Redentore festival, only 60,000 guests were admitted to the place of action.
In addition, a moratorium on the creation of new hotels and fast food restaurants in the historic part of Venice has been introduced.
