Electricity is cheaper for both residents and producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (East Siberia) to establish fair tariffs for electric energy consumers, which have been fulfilled for decades, are beginning to produce fruit.
From September 1, the cost of electricity in low voltage for industrial recipients is reduced by 25%.
Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Resolution of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the wholesale market of electric energy and power and in the summary forecast balance of production and supply of electric energy (power) within the framework of the Unified Energy System of Russia by subjects of the Russian Federation" (from 17.07.2017. No 842) has established indicative prices for electricity and capacity for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryatia.
As a result, the cost of electric energy for Buryat producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the life of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the republic have offended the thresholds of Moscow offices in vain attempts to equalize the region in tariffs with the neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power plants in Angara, flowing from Baikal, the main watershed area for which Buryatia is.
And only this year began the moves.
In March, the tariffs for electric energy for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles/kWh to 3.93 rubles/kWh, or 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the List of the territories of the wholesale market price zones, for which the peculiarities of the functioning of wholesale and retail markets are established is the turn of industrial consumers.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, since the population of the Irkutsk region pays for kilowatts/hour of 1.01 rubles.
But no one dares to name at least the approximate date of the new tariff moves towards a downgrade for Buryatia.
