In Ukraine, offered to send Russians to prison for illegal border crossing
In the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine registered a draft law, according to which in the country may appear criminal punishment for Russians for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to the RT channel, the document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament involves a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens trying to illegally enter the territory of the country.
It is noted that for a repeated offense or act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment can be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained on the border with weapons, the time of imprisonment for him will increase to eight years.
Earlier it was reported that Ukrainian border guards detained Ukrainians who tried to get into Russia outside the established checkpoints.
