Two new territories of advancing socio-economic development will appear in Russia - Abaz and Novotroitsk.
The relevant resolutions of the Government of the Russian Federation will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity ofTORa on the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia have been determined.
In the city where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activities, as well as the minimum amount of capital investments of residents, the minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is assumed that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments in the city, as well as more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities, in which the TOP "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activities, for example, included crop production, livestock, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already now the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise of "Abakan mine."
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development to create a TOP.
The authorities of the Orenburg region also acted in a similar way.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk will also create an area of advancing socio-economic development.
This will diversify the economy of the monotown, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise of JSC "Ural Steel," as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 mm million rubles.
The list of economic activities, in which the new TOP will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs, includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monotowns of the Orenburg region, which received the status of TOP.
Recall that the area of advancing development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investments to improve the life of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of TOR can be allocated the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% for the first five years, and not less than 10% for the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential mode of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
